
2.8.3j patch-level 1
 o Temple doesn't sell books anymore; book shop only buys books.
 o Random character/attribute options added to birth.
 o Fixed faulty vault layout (Greg Wooledge).
 o Now prints home details after death instead of black market stock.
 o Infamous save-file '2.8.3c' bug fixed.
 o Added Tim Baker's 'easy' patch (disabled though).
 o Some (fairly minor) source cleanups/changes.
 o Fixed bug where you could be asked to kill a unique who'd already
   died. If you have a save-file where a quest cannot be completed
   because of this, leave the town level; when you return the quest
   will be marked completed.
 o It's now not possible to wield quest items multiple times to receive
   multiple gifts (eg. Sting).
 o Various spells could destroy staircases ; fixed
 o Added Greg Wooledge's patch for glibc2.1/egcs systems
 
2.8.3j
 o Can now wield item from floor to complete a quest.
 o Screen not always refreshed in casino; fixed.
 o Rogue-like commands wouldn't work in new buildings. Hopefully fixed.
 o Extra shopkeepers added (previously, Black Market and Bookstore had
   the same owners).
 o Fixed/added a few prototypes. Some functions called with too many
   arguments, etc.
 o Few other minor alterations.
